ome.smuggler.core.msg

Interface Reschedulable<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageRepeater, OnceOffSchedule, SessionKeepAliveHandler

    public interface Reschedulable<T>
    A task that consumes a channel sink's output and optionally requests the channel to deliver again some more data at a later point in time.
    See Also:
    ReschedulingSink

    • Method Detail

      • consume

        java.util.Optional<Schedule<T>> consume(CountedSchedule current,
                                        T data)
        Consumes the output of the channel this instance is bound to.
        Parameters:
        current - information about this invocation's schedule.
        data - the data received from the channel.
        Returns:
        when and what data to input again in the channel or empty if no further action is required. Never return null.
